727525f-a.folder: Northern Boulevard & Little Neck Parkway, Queens, NY
727525f-a.original_title: Queens: Northern Boulevard - Little Neck Parkway
727525f-a.text:
Northern Boulevard, south side, between Little Neck Parkway, and Glenwood Street, showing the Van Nostrand farmhouse. This individual owned land just east of Little Neck Road and south to West End Drive. There is a large two story structure still on the premises which may be one of his old buildings. The 1909 atlas shows seven frame structures on his land, one of which is this house.

In 1928, Penbrooke Avenue was extended through the center of the property.

About 1890.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

727266f-a.folder: Little Neck Parkway & Northern Boulevard, Queens, NY
727266f-a.original_title: Queens: Little Neck Parkway - Northern Boulevard
727266f-a.text:
Little Neck Parkway, east side, south of Northern Boulevard, showing, in the foreground, a former hotel operated by Van Nostrand and Company in 1896. John Hoagland ran the Hotel about 1875 and one spell later. Van Nostrand conducted a  general store, to the right of the hotel, with B. W. Schenck. They sold out to Sutphin Brothers in 1895. The Manhattan Bank Branch is said to be on the site in 1934. This is a set of two views taken at slightly different angles.

June 1924

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
